	     Bissau - Eighteen people were killed and another 14 injured in the small west African state of Guinea-Bissau late on Friday when a minibus collided with a truck, police and hospital sources said. One witness said the truck appeared to have been speeding when the driver lost control and collided head-on with the minibus near Bissauzinho, around 15km from the capital Bissau. Hospital sources said at least 10 of the injured were in a serious condition. Guinea-Bissau, which lies between Senegal and Guinea, is one of the poorest countries in the world. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  